text: welcome to let's talk a premier Learning
Centre for English communication skills
making you speak fluent English
with neutral accent preposition a
preposition is a word placed before a
noun or a pronoun to show in what
relation the person or thing is to
another part of the sentence the
following are the most common
prepositions in on act off off by 2 into
from up down out with 4 since over
behind between through inside now let's
make some sentences using prepositions
there is a cow in the field in this
sentence the preposition in is
connecting the noun cow to another noun
field he is fond of coffee in this
sentence the preposition off is
connecting the noun to an adjective the
cat jumped of the chair
in this sentence the preposition off is
connecting the noun to a verb let us now
see some simple prepositions I am tired
of waiting at the office he often works
at night he will start at 10 o'clock in
the morning the book you are looking for
is in the shelf
Sooni lives in the village fill the mug
with milk I wrote the letter
with a new pen a train is passing
through the tunnel he has an umbrella
over his head the police car is racing
between two buses the girl is hiding her
face behind the photo frame we went to
watch a cricket game the boy is diving
into the swimming pool the picnic group
is standing on the bridge the goodies
are inside the basket
